post_text: It is National Arts in Education Week!! The healing and unifying power of the arts has been evident as the COVID-19 pandemic swept the country. We have seen and heard it play out through works of art on sidewalks, shared musical moments from porches, in plays and dance performances, and every other imaginable iteration of art making. Our country, our states, and our communities are facing challenges unlike any we have seen before. When intertwining the arts in and through education, research shows that we are better preparing our future leaders to face these difficulties. IC Imagine is proud to be a Fine Arts focused school and we will be spotlighting our fantastic Fine Arts teachers and their programs throughout the week. Join us in celebrating Arts in Education!

We are receiving reports that some teachers and students are receiving an error message when trying to login to https://zoom.us. The issue appears to be with the vendor, as we are not the only institution reporting the error message.

If you experience any issues with Zoom this morning, please keep trying using the downloaded versions of Zoom (chrome app, desktop client, Zoom phone app).

If your student is not able to login to their morning check in/ homeroom meeting, please have them email their homeroom teacher.

We are hopeful that this issue will be resolved quickly, so keep trying for the other scheduled Zoom meetings throughout the day!

post_text: CONGRATULATIONS to IC Imagine band student Sara Nell Chase! For the second year in a row, Sara Nell qualified for All-State Band, and is the only string bass player in the state of North Carolina to earn that honor. This weekend should have been her opportunity to attend a clinic and prepare a concert with other members of the ensemble, but we would still like to recognize her outstanding accomplishment. Great work Sara Nell and thank you for being an amazing representative of the IC Imagine band program and entire school community!

post_text:
A big thank you to all of the healthcare workers out there! We appreciate the sacrifices you are making for those in need.
A special shoutout to one of our seniors, Corin Lueck, who has begun working as a HUC CNA in the Cardiosurgical Unit. Corin has been on the path toward working in medicine for a while and earned his CNA last summer. In the fall he will be attending Carolina where he will major in Biology with a Pre-Med track! We know the staff and patients at Mission are lucky to have him on their side and we are so proud of him. Thank you for your hard work out there Corin!

Upper School Students & Families, remember that you can log into your SCOIR account to find virtual college tour options!

Current upper school students can use SCOIR to...
Compare up to 4 colleges side-by-side to get a high-level overview of admissions, student life, academics, and cost statistics. Move colleges of interest to MyColleges.
Fill out your profile to help your parent/guardian and/or counselor understand you beyond your grades and test scores.
Search for colleges based on your preferences or advanced search. Then, create a list of schools that you want to follow, will apply to, and have applied to in MyColleges.
Virtually tour colleges to gain a feel for the campus environment with YouVisit.
Take the YouScience assessment and receive a detailed report on your talents, link them to potential careers, and save related majors to your Scoir profile.
https://scoir.litmos.com/account/login/?

post_text:
Imagine Families,

Mark Johnson, the state superintendent has shared with all school leaders that North Carolina Governor, Roy Cooper, has ordered the closure of all schools in North Carolina beginning on Monday. As you know, we previously had decided to close school on Monday so our teachers can have time to work through a plan to continue learning remotely. The NC Governor‚Äôs office and NC Superintendent have scheduled a webinar for school leaders tomorrow afternoon to provide more guidance for this situation. As always we will communicate with you regularly as we learn more and implement plans. Please continue to look for more information from us in the days to come.

The NC Governor‚Äôs office and NC Superintendent have scheduled a webinar for school leaders tomorrow afternoon to provide more guidance for this situation. As always we will communicate with you regularly as we learn more and implement plans. Please continue to look for more information from us in the days to come.

As you can see, our biggest current needs are packs of thick markers, and composition notebooks! These can be dropped off at the front desk!
